I need to calculate the Gross Profit Margin based on the income statement provided.

The Gross Profit Margin formula is:
Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

From the income statement:
- Gross Profit = $1,340,513.79
- Total Revenue = $6,920,513.79

Calculating the Gross Profit Margin:
Gross Profit Margin = ($1,340,513.79 / $6,920,513.79) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 0.1937 × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 19.37%

Therefore, the Gross Profit Margin is 19.37%.
